Sentencas: In general, transition metal-doped La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 (LSF) has been used as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) because of its high mixed electronic-ionic conductivity and catalytic properties.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Recently, some research groups have been investigating the doped LSF as an anode material.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In this study, we evaluated the influence of dopant in LSF on anodic properties of LSF in SOFCs.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Whereas Mn-doped LSF showed typical perovskite oxide structure even after reduction in hydrogen at high temperature, the LSF and Co-doped LSF exhibited phase transition partially to LaSrFeO4 and exsolution of metal particles after reduction.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The phase transition and metal exsolution occurred at temperature higher than 1008 K in a reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Despite the partial phase transition, the cell using Co-doped LSF anode exhibited fairly high power density of 1.33 W/cm(2) at 1173 K with the lowest polarization resistance.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: These results may originate from the high oxygen-ion conductivity of LaSrFeO4-La(Sr)Fe(Co)O-3 and the high hydrogen oxidation property of the Co-Fe particles on ceramic anode surface.
Titulo: Phase transition of doped LaFeO3 anode in reducing atmosphere and their power generation property in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
